defaultThis evidence is submitted on 
defaulta corporate basis by Equality Challenge Unit
default (ECU)
default. 
defaultECU i
defaults a charity which works to further and support equality and diversity for staff and students in higher education across all four nations of the UK, and in colleges in Scotland. ECU receives its core 
defaultfunding from 
defaultUniversities UK, GuildHE, the Higher Education Funding Council for England, the Higher Education Funding Council for Wales, the Scottish Funding Council and the Department for Employment and Learning in Northern Ireland.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultAthena SWAN CharterdefaultOne of ECU’s core activities is the Athena SWAN Charter. 
defaultFounded in 2005, the Athena SWAN Charter is a scheme that recognises excellence in science, engineering
default, 
defaulttechnology
default, mathematics and medicine (STEMM
default) employment
default for women in higher education.
default 
defaultThe 
defaultCharter receives addition
defaultal
default funding from the Royal Society, the Biochemical Society, the Department of Health and the Scottish Funding Council.
defaultAny university or research institute embedded within a university that is committed to the advancement of the ca
defaultreers of women 
defaultin STEMM 
defaultcan become a member of the Charter, accepting and promoting the six Charter principles:
defaultThere are currently 
default91
default members of the Charter. Once Charter signatories, universities and their S
defaultTEMM 
defaultdepartments are encouraged to submit for Athena SWAN Charter recognition awards at Bronze, Silver or Gold level.
defaultThe Charter recognises the commitment of universities and university departments to reduce the
default 
defaultdecline in the numbers 
defaultof women in 
defaultS
defaultTEMM
default ac
defaultademic careers 
defaultfurther up the career ladder, and 
defaultretain women graduates and PhD students in academic careers
default.
defaultThis response is based on ECU’s work, in particular the experience of working with universities on Athena SWAN.
